n limits ecosystem processes, while too much nitrogen transforms ecosystems profoundly. The California Nitrogen Assessment is the first comprehensive account of nitrogen flows, practices, and policies for California, encompassing all nitrogen flows—not just those associated with agriculture—and their impacts on ecosystem services and human wellbeing. How California handles nitrogen issues will be of interest nationally and internationally, and the goal of the assessment is to link science with action and to produce information that affects both future policy and solutions for addressing nitrogen pollution. This book also provides a model for application of integrated ecosystem assessment methods at regional and state (subnational) levels.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aBiodiversity conservationzCalifornia. 0aNitrogen cyclexEnvironmental aspectszCalifornia. 0aNitrogen fertilizersxGovernment policyzCalifornia. 0aNitrogenxEnvironmental aspectszCalifornia. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aagriscience.  aair pollution.  aair quality.  abiodiversity conservation.  abiodiversity.  acalifornia agriculture.  acalifornias nitrogen cycle.  aclimate change.  aclimate science.  aecology.  aenvironmental science.  aintegrated ecosystem assessment.  alife sciences.  anitrogen and climate change.  anitrogen cycle.  anitrogen emissions.  anitrogen fertilizers.  anitrogen flows.  anitrogen.  apollution california.  ascientists.  ause of nitrogen.  awater pollution california.1 aBaerenklau, K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrodt, S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChampetier, A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDahlgren, R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vo